caption.text: ‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ thank you to all 27 special people of ARMOUR @pptibca4 for going through the agonizing yet fun cawu 2 üò≠ especially aljel for letting me trash a lot at their place, yove for letting me bug until late at night (and helping me wash dishes when i had freaky finger cut), difa for memes and difastar and food, yudi, ravian, wennie, for taking the troublesome me in bgh during calculus and oop project, anthony for working so hard on calculus for everyone's sake! phew and here i am today being emotional... and i'm writing all this here so i won't forget in the future. üò• cheers to a better trimester ahead! ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢

‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢ last night i had a dream where @martinalarasati came to pick me up at my house abruptly, saying, "oi udah lah brenti belajar, lu kapan keluar rumahnya kalo gini?" and my roommate was trying to defend me in my place, explaining how hard the exams we're going thru and that we need to study, but emel persisted still and finally took me out in her car. she drove straight to perempatan alazhar and took a left turn where we settled to eat at Fish Streat (which is, actually nonexistent) and there we spoke. she said i need to take a break from all the confusing and stressful studying, and like, i have very few time to spend with my friends because of that. she also pointed out that exams are mere scores, she said i'll do just fine in my exams because she /believes/ in me and last but not least she said that "friends will be a more valuable treasure than my gpa at @pptibca4 so start stepping out more and get back to the social life". i guess the dream was a big slap in the face and i feel like i should apologize to everyone i tend to ignore and miss their birthdays or updates and stuff though i don't mean to, really! but anyways. thanks a lot for the late bday gift, @martinalarasati and thanks for showing up in my dreams and taking me to fish streat. i think you were the one who paid too. üòè ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢
